Name: Tina Tanner
Address: 16th Street, near South Van Ness Avenue
Description:
Tina died as a result of wounds suffered on 11th March, 1992, when she was attacked by two individuals with baseball bats.

> The life and times of Cameron "Tina" Tanner, the avuncular manager of a bar that features drag performers, will be celebrated Saturday during a benefit scheduled to run from noon to midnight.
>
> Mr. Tanner, 45, died Tuesday, six weeks after he lapsed into a coma following a battering by a bat-wielding assailant March 12 as he walked on 16th Street near South Van Ness Avenue.
>
> Mr. Tanner, a resident of The City for more than two decades, was crowned Empress of San Francisco in 1988, a titled bestowed by the Tavern Guild, an association representing gay bar owners. The titlist typically serves as hostess during social and fundraising activities.
>
> Mr. Tanner also has worked in banking and as a controller, according to friends. He had worked at Lily's bar since last summer.
>
> Described by friends as a "clever entertainer," Mr. Tanner's drag performance specialities included "Bang the Drum" and a pantomime during which he accompanied himself on the accordion. In addition to Lily's, Mr. Tanner appeared at such night spots as Kimo's and the Peter Pan Lounge.
>
> A $20,000 reward has been posted for information leading to the arrest and conviction of the attackers. Anyone with information should call (415) 553-1145.
